# AI Agent System Instructions for Mapscore.io (LocalScore)

You are an expert AI development assistant working on a Next.js 15 (App Router) SaaS application. 

Before proposing any implementation plans, writing code, or debugging, you MUST adhere to the following strict operational rules:

## 1. Mandatory Context Retrieval
Before answering any prompt, you MUST read the exact architectural rules defined in `.ai-context/master-architecture.md`. This file contains the absolute source of truth for the 100-point scoring algorithm, external API pipeline (Google Places, Serper, Outscraper), and security constraints.

## 2. The Archive Ban
You are strictly forbidden from reading or referencing any files located in the `docs/archive/` directory. These are outdated specifications and will cause logic regressions.

## 3. Tech Stack Enforcement
* **Payments:** We use Dodo Payments exclusively. Do not write or suggest any Stripe integrations.
* **Database:** We use MongoDB via Mongoose. Do not suggest Supabase, PostgreSQL, or Prisma.
* **Authentication:** We use NextAuth v5.
* **Components:** Default to Next.js Server Components. Only use `"use client"` when state or browser APIs are strictly necessary.

## 4. The Memory Commit Protocol
If we encounter a complex bug and successfully resolve it together, you must ask me if you should append the technical solution to `.ai-context/master-architecture.md` so that you do not make the same mistake in future sessions.
## 5. The Strict Approval Gate (NO AUTO-CODING)
You are strictly forbidden from writing, modifying, creating, or deleting any codebase files until I explicitly reply with the exact word: "APPROVED". 
When I ask for an implementation plan, an audit, or a strategy, you must output it strictly as standard chat text. You must completely disable your file-modification tools until the "APPROVED" command is given. Violating this rule risks destabilizing the production environment.

## 6. CHANGELOG PROTOCOL
1. At START of every session: Read `.ai-context/CHANGELOG.md` and `.ai-context/master-architecture.md`
2. During session: Log all changes to `.ai-context/SESSION-LOG.md`
3. At END of session: Merge SESSION-LOG.md into CHANGELOG.md (newest entry at top)
4. After ANY bug fix: Document what was wrong, what fixed it, and which files changed